The problem here is that you are assigning to part of `total_results` during the loop, but not in a [&quot;sliced&quot;][1] manner. It&#39;s probably simpler to collect up the names and values separately, and then use [`cell2struct`][2] after the `parfor` loop, like this:

    N = 10;
    names = cell(1, N);
    results = cell(1, N);
    parfor i = 1:10
        name = sprintf(&#39;result_%i&#39;,i)
        names{i} = name;
        results{i} = struct(&#39;a&#39;, rand(i), &#39;b&#39;, rand(i));
    end
    total_results = cell2struct(results, names, 2);
    
*EDIT* another way of slicing the outputs (as suggested in the comments) is to use

    parfor i = 1:10
        total_results(i).result = struct(&#39;a&#39;, rand(i), &#39;b&#39;, rand(i));
    end

In this case, this works because the first-level indexing expression is a &quot;sliced&quot; expression.


  [1]: https://uk.mathworks.com/help/parallel-computing/sliced-variable.html
  [2]: https://uk.mathworks.com/help/matlab/ref/cell2struct.html

