answers.body_markdown:
You need [copy.deepcopy()][1]. When creating the members of the 2-d array you were copying over the same 1-d array object, so the assignment for `pole[0][0]` was assigning to `pole[1][0]` as well, etc.

    #!/usr/bin/env python3
    import copy
    def prog2():
            x = int(input(&#39;x&gt; &#39;))
            y = int(input(&#39;y&gt; &#39;))
            pole = [[0] * x]
            for i in range(1, y):
                pole.append(copy.deepcopy(pole[0]))
            for a in range(x):
                for b in range(y):
                    pole[a][b] = int(input(&#39;&gt; &#39;))
    
            print(pole)
    prog2()


  [1]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/copy.html?highlight=copy#module-copy

